        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="fGithubActions" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;" value="GitHub Actions&#xa;CI: lint, typecheck, test, build" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="50" width="220" x="40" y="460" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="fSentry" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;" value="Sentry&#xa;error monitoring (API + Web)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="50" width="220" x="40" y="530" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="fDeployTargets" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=10;fontStyle=2;align=left;" value="CD: EC2+ALB (API, live) · Vercel + Amplify parallel run (Web, cutover pending)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="20" width="220" x="40" y="595" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="implNotes" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;fillColor=none;strokeColor=#444444;" value="Implementation notes (trimmed from boxes above — verified against code 2026-06-30)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="220" width="940" x="320" y="960" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="implNotesText" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;align=left;verticalAlign=top;" value="• Auth: JWT + Google/GitHub OAuth.&#xa;• Feedback: public submissions go through throttling + API-key &amp; origin whitelist (validated via CreatePublicFeedbackDto + global ValidationPipe, content ≤5000 chars); saves to Postgres synchronously, then enqueues a BullMQ job (if plan allows AI).&#xa;• Billing: Stripe webhooks at /webhooks/stripe.&#xa;• AI: BullMQ worker (ai-analysis queue) calls Gemini, writes the result back to Postgres, then emits Socket.io feedbackUpdated.&#xa;• Digest: weekly AI digest — scheduled in-process via @Cron (Mon 09:00). The duplicate EventBridge→Lambda→internal-endpoint trigger was removed 2026-07-03.&#xa;• Events Gateway: single event feedbackUpdated (room team-{teamId}) — emitted after AI analysis, on status update, and on bulk archive. NOT emitted on initial feedback creation.&#xa;• SQS/Lambda feedback-processor stub removed 2026-07-09 (PLAN 🔥 #9) — it only console.log&#39;d the event and shipped no feature; the seam right after feedbackRepository.save() stays in the code for a future real consumer (Slack, analytics).&#xa;• Landing (apps/landing, insightstream.ai): pure marketing Next.js 16 app — zero @insightstream/* deps. All CTAs are plain &lt;a href&gt; links to app.insightstream.ai/auth/register. Registration auto-creates a personal team. See Registration &amp; Onboarding Flow tab." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="900" x="340" y="1000" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="archDecisions" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;fillColor=none;strokeColor=#444444;" value="Architecture Decisions" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="450" width="380" x="1300" y="90" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="archDecisionsText" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;align=left;verticalAlign=top;" value="• Monorepo (pnpm + Turbo) — share types/DB entities across apps without publishing packages.&#xa;• PostgreSQL over MongoDB — relational data (users/projects/teams/feedback) benefits from FK integrity and TypeORM tooling.&#xa;• BullMQ (Redis) for AI analysis — decouples slow Gemini calls from the feedback-submission request/response cycle.&#xa;• Socket.io for realtime dashboard updates — pushes AI results and status changes without polling.&#xa;• Stateless API — no session state on EC2, safe to scale horizontally or swap ALB target groups.&#xa;• AWS migration: API (EC2) and DB (RDS) cutover complete; Web (Vercel→Amplify) still a parallel run — see Current vs Target panel on the AWS Infrastructure tab." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="400" width="340" x="1320" y="130" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
